   <conbody>
      <hazardstatement id="Modular-Battery-EPO-ABC8B8B0"
                       type="danger"
                       class="+ topic/note hazard-d/hazardstatement ">
         <messagepanel class="+ topic/ul hazard-d/messagepanel ">
            <typeofhazard class="+ topic/li hazard-d/typeofhazard ">ENERGIZED BY EXTERNAL POWER SOURCES</typeofhazard>
            <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid ">When emergency power off (EPO) is activated the output
breaker is tripped.</howtoavoid>
            <howtoavoid platform="Modular-DC Modular-AC"
                        class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid ">Hazardous voltages are
still present. The system is still energized by the upstream supply
and batteries (unless the system is disconnected from the upstream
supply and the batteries with a separate EPO).</howtoavoid>
            <howtoavoid platform="Modular-Inverter Modular-DCDC-Converter"
                        class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid ">Hazardous
voltages are still present. The system is still energized by the upstream
supply and DC source (unless the system is disconnected from the upstream
supply and the DC source with a separate EPO).</howtoavoid>
         </messagepanel>
      </hazardstatement>
      <p class="- topic/p ">According to UPS safety standard IEC 62040-1, a UPS with an emergency
switch device should be able to prevent further supply of the load.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">The emergency switching device interrupts the load via a terminal
to an externally connected switching device. The EPO in a Reality Modular
system will trip the output breaker(s).</p>
      <note class="- topic/note ">All modules in the system are still in operation.</note>
